  ${
    $d F x y $.  $d G x y $.  $d H x y $.
    ghomid.1 $e |- U = ( Id ` G ) $.
    ghomid.2 $e |- T = ( Id ` H ) $.
    $( A group homomorphism maps identity element to identity element.
       (Contributed by Paul Chapman, 3-Mar-2008.) $)
    ghomid $p |- ( ( G e. GrpOp /\ H e. GrpOp /\ F e. ( G GrpHom H ) ) ->
                   ( F ` U ) = T ) $=
